cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on wireless sensor networks and their energy management. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper proposes a system model and optimization problem to achieve optimal trade-off between rate utility and electricity cost. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper considers channel conditions as one of the stochastic natures affecting the system. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is relevant as the paper proposes a fully distributed and low-complexity cross-layer algorithm. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also relevant as the proposed algorithm is distributed and low-complexity.
